      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The city *can* allow for variances, but this is not automatic; it requires a formal application and demonstration that you have a hardship that doesn't stem from your own design choices. For a tiny encroachment, you might have a better chance, but if it impacts the public right-of-way, the city often has strict rules to prevent public disruption. It is best to consult with a planning professional early on to see if a minor deviation is justifiable before you build anything.",
